did.unittitle: Associated Students of Stanford University records
did.abstract: The records include correspondence, minutes, reports, financial records, and other materials arranged in the following series: President's Correspondence (1919-1971), Legislative Records (1891-1998), Student Manager (1924-1963), Treasurer (1939-1992), General Files (1936-1992), Organizations (1925-1990), Course Guides (1965-1980), and Additional Records (1984-2006).

accessrestrict.head: Information about Access
accessrestrict.p: The collection is open for research; materials must be requested at least 48 hours in advance of intended use.

userestrict.head: Ownership & Copyright
userestrict.p: All requests to reproduce, publish, quote from, or otherwise use collection materials must be submitted in writing to the Head of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, California 94304-6064. Consent is given on behalf of Special Collections as the owner of the physical items and is not intended to include or imply permission from the copyright owner. Such permission must be obtained from the copyright owner, heir(s) or assigns. See: http://library.stanford.edu/depts/spc/pubserv/permissions.html.
Restrictions also apply to digital representations of the original materials. Use of digital files is restricted to research and educational purposes.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical Sketch
bioghist.p: The Associated Students of Stanford University (ASSU) was organized in October 1891; each registered student is a member. The ASSU works to represent the interests, needs and perspectives of Stanford students.

scopecontent.head: Description of the Collection
scopecontent.p: The records include correspondence, minutes, reports, financial records, and other materials arranged in the following series: President's Correspondence (1919-1971), Legislative Records (1891-1998), Student Manager (1924-1963), Treasurer (1939-1992), General Files (1936-1992), Organizations (1925-1990), Course Guides (1965-1980), and Additional Records (1984-2006).

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: The President's records consist largely of correspondence but also include some reports, memoranda, agenda, minutes, and other materials. Typical subjects include athletics, social events (concerts, dances, etc.), the Honor Code and Fundamental Standard, ASSU elections and committee meetings, public service and philanthropy efforts (often filed under "Drives"), the student union, and relations with student governments at other universities. Stanford agencies often represented in the records include Stanford Alumni Association, Stanford Fund (and other fundraising groups), Dean of Men, Dean of Women, Dean of Students, President's Office, other student associations (such as the Interfraternity Council, Institute for International Relations, KZSU, and Ram's Head), and the Stanford Bookstore. There is also frequently correspondence with the National Student Federation of America (1930s-1940s), the National Students Association (1950s-1960s), the Pacific Student Presidents Association, and the World Student Service Fund (1940s). Finally, there are unique subjects relevant to the historic era: Civil Defense during World War II and the political unrest of the 1960s-1970s.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Legislative records contain agendas, minutes, memoranda, resolutions, reports, correspondence and other materials of the ASSU Senate and various committees; the ASSU constitution and by-laws along with revisions and amendments; election handbooks and other election materials; and files on the Honor Code, the Student Conduct Legislative Council, and the judicial system in general.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Bound volume contains correspondence, reports, various papers on the topic presented to campus groups, questionnaires, transcripts of two panel discussions arranged by the Men's and Women's Councils 1936, clippings, and other materials.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: The Student Manager records consist largely of bound volumes of reports from or about various clubs, committees, or events in an academic year. Detailed lists of contents for each volume are included in the listing that follows. Bound student police reports for 1939-1963 are also in this series. The responsibilities of the student police were largely crowd control at campus events; their duties included monitoring behavior, handling tickets, controlling parking and traffic, and keeping out gate crashers. The reports list the student police on duty, sometimes the various tasks, and usually include a paragraph or two on the event itself. Many of the entries are from The Sunday Flicks.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series largely consists of bound reports from the Dramatic Council and the Publications Council. The Dramatic Council reports, 1925-1941, include expenses, budgets, contracts, some correspondence, minutes, and narrative reports. The Publications Council reports, 1931-1932 and 1938-1967, include financial information on the Chaparral, Quad, and Daily, and Publications Council minutes. Records for the 1932/33 through 1938/39 academic years are included in Student Manager's reports in Series 3. Other records in this series include bound volumes containing constitutions and by-laws of student organizations, 1920-1963, and miscellaneous files from the Publications Council.
